Dr. Aryani earned her dental degree from the New York University College of Dentistry in 2003. She serves honorably in the USAF as a Captain in Dental Corp, right after graduating. Throughout her 20 year career, she has kept up-to-date with more than a 1000 hours of continuing education classes to ensure her patients receive the most comprehensive &amp; advanced care. She is also a graduate of the prestigious Dawson Academy and is a fellow of AAOSH (American Academy of Oral Systemic Health)and a member of IABDM (International Academy of Biological Dentistry and Medicine).

Dr. Aryani practices the concept of “holistic,  biologic dentistry and functional orthodontic”,  which focuses on getting to the root cause of patient care - emphasizing prevention &amp; early intervention. This practice philosophy requires understanding that there is a connection between systemic disease and oral conditions. Did you know, for example, that 50% of all heart attacks are caused by periodontal pathogens and that diseases such as diabetes, high blood pressure, heart attacks, ADHD, depression, obesity and sleep apnea can have their roots traced to airway issues, tongue position and the development of the upper and lower jaws. So addressing the oral systemic link could save you from many systemic problems in the future. Dr. Aryani identifies these issues before any symptoms appear, so you can get and remain healthy.

&nbsp;

“I became a dentist because I love helping people.  Helping them smile confidently makes my world and their’s a lot brighter.”
&nbsp;
Dr. Bender’s greatest satisfaction comes from enriching the lives of her patients with truly high quality dental care. A perfectionist through and through, Dr. Bender will place a great deal of effort into making sure your experience is comfortable, stress free, fun, and friendly. She recognizes the important connection between your oral health and your overall well-being, which is why Dr. Bender is so passionate about the art of dentistry. Dr. Bender’s all-inclusive approach helps her patients improve their lives by giving them a new, beautiful smile, or by simply providing them with the continuing care and education needed to maintain their already healthy smile.
&nbsp;
In her ongoing quest to provide her patients with the highest level of dental care, Dr. Bender, the Edmond dentist, furthers her skills by participating in continuing education opportunities in the latest dental techniques and technologies. She is currently active in the Spears Education Center and Spears Study Club. The art of dentistry is always advancing, and Dr. Bender stays on the leading edge of that advancement so she can provide amazing dental treatments that enrich her patients’ lives. Her greatest success is in creating an environment free of fear and embarrassment where patients are amazed by the healthy, happy smiles she creates.
&nbsp;
Dr. Bender received her undergraduate biology degree from the University of Central Oklahoma, where she was a collegiate athlete, playing women’s basketball. Soon after, she earned her Doctor of Dental Surgery degree from the University of Oklahoma, College of Dentistry. Dr. Bender is an active member of the American Academy of Cosmetic Dentists, American Dental Association, Oklahoma Dental Association, American Women’s Dental Association, and Oklahoma County Dental Society.
&nbsp;
Through the Give-Back-A-Smile Program, Dr. Bender volunteers her time to helping restore the smiles of domestic abuse victims, re-establishing their confidence and health as they rebuild their lives. She also volunteers for Oklahoma Mission of Mercy “OK Moms,” an annual 2-day event providing free dental care to as many adults and children as time will allow.

Dr. Kelly J. Blodgett is Oregon's only Certified Biological Dentist both by the IABDM and the International Institute of Biological Dentistry.  He is one of the world's most recognized experts in the field of biological dentistry and holistic oral health. His career has been marked with a bevy of national and international awards. He in not only an exceptionally gifted clinician, but also a gifted communicator.  He is leading the profession of dentistry to an approach that focuses on the humanistic emotions and feelings that accompany healthcare experiences.

His upcoming book, "Feel Whole Again," is revolutionizing the approach to oral health care and redefining the modern dental experience.  His approach starts with humanizing dental visits by dealing first and foremost with the toxic emotions that people carry from their past dental experiences. He uses the goals, values, timeline and budget of each unique human being he treats as the guideposts rather than traditional dental dogma. Dr. Blodgett's mantra of "First psychology, then biology optimized by technology" has helped thousands of human beings reclaim not only their physical health, but their mental and emotional balance, as well.  Prepare yourself for a time of self-discovery and health optimization as you realize the power of the humanistic modern dental experience at Blodgett Dental Care!

&nbsp;

Dr. Puneet Brar is the owner and the head dentist. She bought this practice in February of 2020 but has worked at several dental practices in the United States. She has been practicing in Las Vegas Nevada for 4 years now.  She attended Boston University and graduated in 2015 with her dentistry degree. 
&nbsp;
Dr. Brar loves Dentistry and loves helping people with there health. Hobbies include Hiking, being in nature and learning new things.

While living in Milwaukee with my wife and newborn son, I graduated from Marquette University in 1972. I joined the U.S. Air Force and served as a captain in the dental division of Scott Air Force base near St. Louis, Missouri. After serving in the Air Force our family of four, soon to be five, moved to Pierce County where we still reside. Shortly after moving to the area my dental practice gradually evolved from traditional dentistry into a more holistic philosophy. During my first five years of private practice in Ellsworth, WI. I came to believe that there was more to dentistry than what I had been taught.
&nbsp;
I began a path of continuing education that has taken me through advanced training in TMJ therapy, orthopedic orthodontics, cranial sacral therapy, bodywork / massage, nutrition, pain management, safe amalgam removal, biological / environmental dentistry, and more. I am still on that path of continuing education and I learn more all the time, spending 200 – 300 hours in class every year. Recently I've been publishing original material in article and textbook formats, as well as creating education materials for doctors and patients.
&nbsp;
I'm looking forward to our new office, and being able to give our patients even better care. Caring for my patients and helping them reach their health goals is what drives me everyday.

Dr. Craig Simmons graduated from Marquette University School of Dentistry and went on to serve in the United States Navy as a dentist for three years. During that time he also earned a degree in Advanced Education in General Dentistry.
&nbsp;
Dr. Simmons has been in private practice for more than seven years and is continuing to expand his practice in holistic dentistry. He is a member of the Holistic Dental Association and a Certified Biological Dentist with the International Academy of Biological Dentistry and Medicine.
&nbsp;
Since he began practicing dentistry, Dr. Simmons is up to date on many continuing educational classes, ensuring that his patients receive the most comprehensive and advanced dental care.
&nbsp;
He and his wife Nicole have four boys and enjoy many outdoor sports. You will appreciate his skill in metal-free crown and bridge work, composite-resin filling placement, and oral surgery techniques, including osseous surgery.

